{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019wQLAMDr7wgyaKFn2vG9ea","type":"tool_result","content":"  2450→---\n  2451→\n  2452→## Session 15 Retrospective — 2026-03-25T11:37Z\n  2453→\n  2454→### 1. Session Summary\n  2455→\n  2456→| Story | Outcome | Notes |\n  2457→|-------|---------|-------|\n  2458→| (none) | NO_WORK | 9th consecutive no-op session |\n  2459→\n  2460→**Net progress:** Zero. Sprint state unchanged from session 7. 65/66 stories done (98.5%).\n  2461→\n  2462→### 2. Issues Analysis\n  2463→\n  2464→**Critical process issue: Ralph loop not terminating on NO_WORK.**\n  2465→\n  2466→Sessions 7-15 (9 consecutive sessions) have all been no-ops. The only non-done story (14-4-observability-backend-choice) is retry-exhausted (10/10) and flagged. Ralph continues spawning sessions that immediately find no work, burning API credits (~$0.50-1.00 per session for context load + tool calls).\n  2467→\n  2468→**Root cause:** Ralph's loop termination logic does not detect consecutive NO_WORK results. It should stop after 1-2 consecutive no-ops, not continue indefinitely.\n  2469→\n  2470→### 3. What Went Well\n  2471→\n  2472→- Session correctly identified no actionable work in <1 minute\n  2473→- No wasted subagent invocations\n  2474→\n  2475→### 4. What Went Wrong\n  2476→\n  2477→- This session should not have been spawned at all\n  2478→- 9 no-op sessions = ~$5-9 wasted on API calls with zero output\n  2479→\n  2480→### 5. Lessons Learned\n  2481→\n  2482→- Ralph needs a consecutive no-op counter with a hard stop (suggest: 2 consecutive NO_WORK results → halt loop)\n  2483→- The flagged stories mechanism works for skipping, but doesn't feed back into loop termination\n  2484→\n  2485→### 6. Action Items\n  2486→\n  2487→- **Fix now:** Ralph loop should read the previous session's result and stop if NO_WORK was returned consecutively\n  2488→- **Fix soon:** Add a `.last_result` file that harness-run writes (e.g., `NO_WORK` or `STORY_DONE:{key}`) so Ralph can make informed loop decisions\n  2489→- **Backlog:** Consider marking epic-14 as `done-with-exceptions` when all non-exhausted stories are done\n  2490→\n  2491→---\n  2492→\n  2493→## Updated End-of-Day Sprint Summary — 2026-03-25 (Final, Session 15)\n  2494→\n  2495→| Metric | Value |\n  2496→|--------|-------|\n  2497→| Stories completed | 65/66 (98.5%) |\n  2498→| Epics completed | 15/16 (Epic 14 has 1 story remaining) |\n  2499→| Stories completed today | 10 (sessions 1-6) |\n  2500→| Total sessions today | 15 (loops 1-15) |\n  2501→| Productive sessions | 6 (sessions 1-6) |\n  2502→| No-op sessions | 9 (sessions 7-15) |\n  2503→| Wasted session ratio | 60% (9/15) |\n  2504→| Remaining blocker | 14-4-observability-backend-choice (Docker keychain, retry-exhausted) |\n  2505→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016bm8Vm35hrwaxcUECzXhDh","session_id":"7abd6544-c701-4823-9983-ef3c4c76fb5b","uuid":"6e0cdfba-cf15-4c7f-98cb-fec5324f5e5f","timestamp":"2026-03-25T07:40:38.773Z"}
