{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016bm8Vm35hrwaxcUECzXhDh","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-25.md`.\n\nKey findings:\n\n**The circuit breaker is broken.** `consecutive_no_progress` stays at 0 because `files_changed` (computed via `git diff`) counts ralph's own state files (`ralph/live.log`, `ralph/status.json`, `.circuit_breaker_state`, etc.) as \"progress.\" Every session modifies these files, so the circuit breaker never trips.\n\n**Three compounding failures** caused 10 no-op sessions:\n1. Circuit breaker false positives from ralph's own file modifications\n2. No \"all-non-flagged-done\" exit condition (65/66 != 66/66, loop continues)\n3. Flagged stories not feeding into loop termination logic\n\n**Three \"fix now\" action items** before next session:\n1. Exclude `ralph/*` and `.circuit_breaker_state` from the `files_changed` git diff count\n2. Add an exit condition: if all non-done stories are flagged, stop the loop\n3. Add a consecutive no-story-change counter (halt after 2 no-ops)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5dc67f73821a7cf9 (use SendMessage with to: 'a5dc67f73821a7cf9' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 43825\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 211254</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7abd6544-c701-4823-9983-ef3c4c76fb5b","uuid":"eda22011-bfde-4820-a796-348e9eacb476","timestamp":"2026-03-25T07:43:53.958Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /retrospective for the current sprint session.\n\nSprint status: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml\nSession issues log: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md\n\nCRITICAL: Read the session issues log FIRST. This file contains real problems, workarounds, bugs, and observations reported by every subagent that ran this session. These are the raw materials for your retrospective — do not ignore them.\n\nKEY CONTEXT: This is the 10th consecutive no-op session. The only non-done story is 14-4-observability-backend-choice which is retry-exhausted (10/10) and flagged. 65/66 stories are done (98.5%). Ralph loop keeps spawning sessions that find no actionable work.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — which stories were attempted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize and analyze all issues from the session log:\n   - Bugs discovered during implementation or verification\n   - Workarounds applied (tech debt introduced this session)\n   - Code quality concerns raised by reviewers\n   - Verification gaps (escalated ACs, weak evidence)\n   - Tooling/infrastructure problems (sandbox, permissions, CLI issues)\n3. **What went well** — stories completed, bugs fixed, process improvements\n4. **What went wrong** — failures, blockers, stuck stories, wasted iterations\n5. **What went wrong** — the ralph loop not terminating after detecting no actionable work\n6. **Lessons learned** — patterns to repeat or avoid\n7. **Action items** — concrete next steps, split into:\n   - Fix now (before next session)\n   - Fix soon (next sprint)\n   - Backlog (track but not urgent)\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-25.md where the date is 2026-03-25.\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"a5dc67f73821a7cf9","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-25.md`.\n\nKey findings:\n\n**The circuit breaker is broken.** `consecutive_no_progress` stays at 0 because `files_changed` (computed via `git diff`) counts ralph's own state files (`ralph/live.log`, `ralph/status.json`, `.circuit_breaker_state`, etc.) as \"progress.\" Every session modifies these files, so the circuit breaker never trips.\n\n**Three compounding failures** caused 10 no-op sessions:\n1. Circuit breaker false positives from ralph's own file modifications\n2. No \"all-non-flagged-done\" exit condition (65/66 != 66/66, loop continues)\n3. Flagged stories not feeding into loop termination logic\n\n**Three \"fix now\" action items** before next session:\n1. Exclude `ralph/*` and `.circuit_breaker_state` from the `files_changed` git diff count\n2. Add an exit condition: if all non-done stories are flagged, stop the loop\n3. Add a consecutive no-story-change counter (halt after 2 no-ops)"}],"totalDurationMs":211254,"totalTokens":43825,"totalToolUseCount":23,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3287,"cache_read_input_tokens":40241,"output_tokens":296,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3287},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
